    <text><body>
            <div type="writingSession">
                <pb n="1r"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000407 https://www.geonames.org/2645740">Kew</placeName> April 26<hi rendition="#sup"><hi rendition="#u">th</hi></hi> 1855.</dateline>
                    <salute>My dear &amp; Venerable friend</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have allowed a very long <lb/>time to pass since the receipt <supplied cert="high">of</supplied>
                    <lb/>the long &amp; kind letter, with <lb/>which you honored me by <lb/><ref xml:id="d5b49af0-d270-41e3-b49a-f0d27081e301" corresp="#c5de245a-9aa2-49e2-9e24-5a9aa209e202" type="editorialNote">Herr <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0015656 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117645281">Schönbein</persName></ref><note xml:id="c5de245a-9aa2-49e2-9e24-5a9aa209e202" corresp="#d5b49af0-d270-41e3-b49a-f0d27081e301" type="editorial"><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011992 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118774891">J.D. Hooker</persName>
                            meint <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0015656 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117645281">Philipp Schönlein</persName>.</note>, but I have <lb/>been anxious to procure for you <lb/>as definite
                    information as I <lb/>can about the <name type="plant" key="Sargassum">Gulf-weed</name>.</p>
                <p>From my own observations, <lb/>made in the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0016294 https://www.geonames.org/3373404">Sargasso
                        Sea</placeName>, <lb/>I concluded that the <hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant">Sargassum</name></hi>
                    <lb/>was <list>
                        <item>1) An <name type="plant">algae</name> in a decidedly <lb/>abnormal
                            state.</item>
                        <item>2) That it <lb/>had certainly been originally <lb/>transported <add place="superlinear">by currents</add> to that meridian.</item>
                        <item>3) That the individual specimens <lb/>were growing with great
                            <lb/>rapidity.</item>
                        <item>4) That they were <lb/>constantly being multiplied by<pb n="1v"/><choice>
                                <orig>by </orig>
                                <reg/>
                            </choice>the multitudes of <name type="animal" key="Fisch">Fish</name>
                            <lb/>&amp; <name type="animal" key="Crustacea">Crustaceae</name> that
                            swarmed <lb/>amongst them.</item>
                        <item>5<choice>
                                <orig><hi rendition="#sup">th</hi></orig>
                                <reg>)</reg>
                            </choice> That <lb/>each piece thus severed <lb/>maintained an
                            independent <lb/>Existence &amp; increased greatly.</item>
                        <item>6) From a study of the subject <lb/>with <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0790354">D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>. Harvey</persName>, after my <lb/>return
                            from the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0002469 https://www.geonames.org/6255152">Antarctic</placeName>
                            <lb/>voyage, I concluded that it <lb/>was specifically the same (but <lb/><subst>
                                <del rendition="#s"><gap reason="illegible" unit="words" quantity="1"/></del>
                                <add place="superlinear">an altered form of)</add>
                            </subst> a <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0010380 https://www.geonames.org/6255150">South America</placeName>n
                            species.</item>
                    </list></p>
                <p>I may further remark <lb/>that the <hi rendition="#u">Macrocystis</hi> floats
                    <lb/>over the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0020731 https://www.geonames.org/4036776">Antarctic Ocean</placeName> in <lb/><add place="superlinear">detached</add> masses far larger than those <lb/>of the
                        <hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant">Sargassum</name></hi>, maintaining
                    <lb/>equally an independent <lb/>life &amp; growing; but always<pb n="2r"/>presenting a different form <lb/>from the <hi rendition="#u">attached</hi>
                    specimens <lb/>of the same <name type="plant" key="algae">Algae</name>. – So
                    also <lb/>in my voyage from the <lb/><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0016294 https://www.geonames.org/3373404">Sargasso
                        sea</placeName> northwards to <lb/>the Channels, I encountered <lb/><hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant">Fucus serratus</name></hi> &amp; <hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant" key="Fucus nodosus">nodosus</name></hi>,
                    <lb/>living in mid-ocean &amp; <lb/>maintaining an independent <lb/>Existence,
                    just as the <hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant">Sargassum</name></hi>
                    <lb/>did – they had <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">no doubt</del>
                        <add place="superlinear">probably</add>
                    </subst>
                    <lb/>been drifted to that meridian <lb/>from the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0001698 https://www.geonames.org/7729890"><choice>
                            <abbr>N.</abbr>
                            <expan>North</expan>
                        </choice> America</placeName>n coast <lb/>&amp; <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">was</del>
                        <add place="superlinear">were</add>
                    </subst> not uncommon.</p>
                <p>I have begun to compile <lb/>a <ref xml:id="e8924743-c92e-4edb-9247-43c92ecedb60" corresp="#cfe1ceea-98dd-441f-a1ce-ea98dd441fe3" type="editorialNote">Flora Arctica</ref><note xml:id="cfe1ceea-98dd-441f-a1ce-ea98dd441fe3" corresp="#e8924743-c92e-4edb-9247-43c92ecedb60" type="editorial">Vgl. <bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/3QT6778E">Hooker, J.D. 1862</bibl>.</note>,
                    from the <lb/>combined materials of all <lb/>the Arctic voyages; it will <lb/>I
                    hope form an interesting <lb/>subject, &amp; will be chiefly<pb n="2v"/>remarkable for the small <lb/>number of Endemic species. <lb/>I am also
                    engaged upon the <lb/><ref xml:id="ad98719e-d2df-4d22-9871-9ed2df9d221f" corresp="#eac66354-0dd2-4369-8663-540dd263695c" type="editorialNote">Flora of Tasmania</ref><note xml:id="eac66354-0dd2-4369-8663-540dd263695c" corresp="#ad98719e-d2df-4d22-9871-9ed2df9d221f" type="editorial"><bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/T5SDE24E">Hooker, J.
                                D. 1844–1860</bibl>, III.</note>, which will <lb/>be accompanied with a sketch <lb/>of the vegetation of
                        <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0002625 https://www.geonames.org/2077456">Australia</placeName><choice>
                        <orig>,</orig>
                        <reg>.</reg>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003944 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117351946">D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>. Thomson</persName>
                    &amp; I have finished <lb/>the first part of our <ref xml:id="f0b0f46e-4de8-4ad6-b0f4-6e4de87ad61b" corresp="#e1f8cc94-6f6a-4e63-b8cc-946f6a8e63e8" type="editorialNote">Flora <lb/>Indica</ref><note xml:id="e1f8cc94-6f6a-4e63-b8cc-946f6a8e63e8" corresp="#f0b0f46e-4de8-4ad6-b0f4-6e4de87ad61b" type="editorial"><bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/VNWTINB4">Hooker, J.
                                D./Thomson 1855</bibl>, I.</note>, which contains a <lb/>long introductory Essay on <lb/>the Physical
                    Geography, <lb/>Botany &amp; Meteorology of all <lb/>the Provinces of <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0006686 https://www.geonames.org/1269750">India</placeName>, from <lb/><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0002330 https://www.geonames.org/1149361">Affghanistan</placeName> to <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0007396 https://www.geonames.org/1814991">China</placeName>,
                    &amp; <lb/>from <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0009370 https://www.geonames.org/1279685">Tibet</placeName> to <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0007287 https://www.geonames.org/1227603">Ceylon</placeName> &amp; <lb/><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0008607">Malacca</placeName>. I hope to have <lb/>the honor of transmitting to
                    <lb/>you a copy of this work <lb/>before many days.</p>
                <p>Mr <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0012148 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118523813">Darwin</persName> is now in very<pb n="3r"/>fair
                    health, though often <lb/>ill for several days at a time. <lb/>He is performing
                    a set of most <lb/>interesting experiments on the <lb/>vitality of seeds after
                    immersion <lb/>in Salt-water which will <lb/>be of the highest importance,
                    <lb/>these observations, &amp; his <ref xml:id="a15fd290-592e-47b1-9fd2-90592e77b178" corresp="#a5fe0fff-2b10-49b2-be0f-ff2b1049b280" type="editorialNote">great <lb/>work on <hi rendition="#uu">Species</hi></ref><note xml:id="a5fe0fff-2b10-49b2-be0f-ff2b1049b280" corresp="#a15fd290-592e-47b1-9fd2-90592e77b178" type="editorial"><bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/63WU32SC">Darwin
                                1859</bibl>.</note>, now occupy <lb/>his attention almost exclusively.</p>
                <p><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003944 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117351946">D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>. Thomson</persName> sailed
                    for <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0016218 https://www.geonames.org/1275004">Calcutta</placeName>
                    <lb/><date when="1855-03" cert="high">a month ago</date>, to relieve <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0020756 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117498246">D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>
                        <lb/>Falconer</persName> at the <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0020399 https://d-nb.info/gnd/2020025-0">Botanic
                        <lb/>Gardens</orgName> of <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0016218 https://www.geonames.org/1275004">Calcutta</placeName>.</p>
                <p>My <persName ref="H0011993">Father</persName> is perfectly well <lb/>&amp;
                    desires his affectionate <lb/>regards, he has hopes of a <lb/><subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">f<gap reason="covered" unit="chars" quantity="3"/></del>
                        <add place="superlinear">large</add>
                    </subst> new Museum being <lb/>built at <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000407 https://www.geonames.org/2645740">Kew</placeName> for the <lb/>illustration of Economic Botany.</p>
                <p><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9236694 https://viaf.org/viaf/198146998388318941056">Mrs Hooker</persName> begs me to present<pb n="3v"/>her
                    most sincere regards <lb/>&amp; respects to you, &amp; to assure <lb/>you how
                    deeply she feels <lb/>the kind &amp; flattering mention <lb/>you make of her.
                    She is <lb/>to me an invaluable wife, <lb/>&amp; worthy of the kind mention
                    <lb/>you always make of her <lb/>industry &amp; love of knowledge. <lb/>Without
                    her I should never <lb/>have been able to get through <lb/>the calculations for
                    my <lb/>Indian observations, the <lb/>means of which she computed <lb/>for me,
                    besides preparing <lb/>the <choice>
                        <abbr>Mss</abbr>
                        <expan>Manuscripts</expan>
                    </choice> of the whole work <lb/>for the press, copying it out, <lb/>&amp;
                    correcting all the proof<lb break="no"/>-sheets three times.</p>
                <p>I have now two little children<supplied cert="high">,</supplied><pb n="4r"/>a
                        <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H6906554">boy</persName> &amp; a <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9813752">girl</persName>, the former of <lb/>whom develops the first <lb/>instinct
                    of man, by digging <lb/>in the garden, before he can <lb/>talk.</p>
                <p>Thus you see my dear friend <lb/>I take you at your word, &amp; <lb/>tell you all
                    about those of <lb/>whom you so kindly ask.</p>
                <p>I have seen much of <ref xml:id="e5d95b2d-a529-4e74-995b-2da5292e748a" corresp="#a0a6720c-2a07-4368-a672-0c2a07536883" type="editorialNote">Herr <lb/><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0015656 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117645281">Schoenbein</persName></ref><note xml:id="a0a6720c-2a07-4368-a672-0c2a07536883" corresp="#e5d95b2d-a529-4e74-995b-2da5292e748a" type="editorial"><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011992 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118774891">J.D. Hooker</persName>
                            meint <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0015656 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117645281">Philipp Schönlein</persName>.</note> &amp; I introduced him <lb/>to those who I hope will be <lb/>of service
                    to him here &amp; in <lb/><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0006686 https://www.geonames.org/1269750">India</placeName>.</p>
                <p>This will be delivered to <lb/>you by Mr <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0016990 http://d-nb.info/gnd/124064272">Bunbury</persName> who <lb/>you <choice>
                        <sic>doubless</sic>
                        <corr>doubtless</corr>
                    </choice> know as the <lb/>brother in law of Herr <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0001895 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118592858">Pertz</persName>, <lb/>&amp; a distinguished Botanist, <lb/>Palaeontologist
                    &amp; traveller. <lb/>He will tell you of poor<pb n="4v"/><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0012188 http://d-nb.info/gnd/116099305">Sir Henry De la Beche</persName>s death <lb/>&amp; of his
                    being succeeded by <lb/><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0014452 http://d-nb.info/gnd/119297345">Sir Roderick
                        Murchison</persName>.</p>
                <p>Mr <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003693 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118674455">Brown</persName> is <add place="superlinear">in</add>
                    very indifferent <lb/>health at present, troubled <lb/>with cough, sleeplessness
                    &amp; <lb/>debility<subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">.</del>
                        <add place="across">,</add>
                    </subst> a change of weather <lb/>will I do not doubt renovate <lb/>his
                    health.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Believe me my kind friend <lb/>with profound respect<choice>
                            <orig>.</orig>
                            <reg/>
                        </choice>
                        <lb/>Your affectionate</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011992 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118774891">Jos. D Hooker</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body></text>
